        </p> -->
        <p class="py-5">
          HDFS stands for Hadoop distributed file systems and is a data center
          that is used to store large amount data and files that are too big to
          store on a single machine. These files are typically in the GB to TB
          range. <br>
          HDFS's architecture is centralized and consists of a Master
          Node, named the NameNode, and thousands of DataNodes. The NameNode
          keeps track how files are split up and where the pieces are stored.
          The DataNodes store the individual data blocks. Multiple DataNodes are
          stacked on top of each other in a rack, and the racks form the data
          center. <br>
          Go to the next page to see how files are split up.
        </p>
      </div>
